15 SECTION 6. ALPR system audits provided by vendor. (1) A vendor that contracts with
16 a law enforcement agency to provide the agency with an automated license plate recognition
17 system or related services shall provide to the agency a monthly audit of the system that is
18 searchable and includes the following information for the preceding 30-day period:
19 (a) The number of automated license plate recognition systems installed, including cam-
20 eras and devices;
21 (b) The location of any fixed or permanent automated license plate recognition system,
22 including cameras and devices;
23 (c) The number of searches of captured license plate data collected by the automated li-
24 cense plate recognition system;
25 (d) A list of any law enforcement agency that has access to the automated license plate
26 recognition system;
27 (e) The number of authorized users for the automated license plate recognition system;
28 (f) The number of unique vehicles captured by the automated license plate recognition
29 system;
30 (g) The number of alerts generated by the automated license plate recognition system;
31 (h) The number of cameras or devices that were accessed or used by the law enforcement
32 agency; and
33 (i) For any search of captured license plate data collected by the automated license plate
34 recognition system:
35 (A) The authorized user identifier of the person who conducts the search;
36 (B) The date and time of the search; and
37 (C) The law enforcement purpose entered for the search.
38 (2) A vendor that contracts with a law enforcement agency to provide the agency with
39 an automated license plate recognition system or related services shall provide to the agency
40 a quarterly audit of the system that is searchable and includes the following information for
41 any search of captured license plate data collected by the automated license plate recognition
42 system that is conducted during the preceding quarter on behalf of any government agency
43 or entity that is not the law enforcement agency:
44 (a) The authorized user identifier of the person who conducts the search;
45 (b) The law enforcement agency that employs the person who conducts the search;
